description: Number of non-unitary but squarefree divisors of binomial(n,floor(n/2)). Also number of nonsquarefree but unitary divisors of binomial(n,floor(n/2)).
example: n=14, C(14,7)=3432, has 32 divisors, 16 unitary, 16 squarefree. The size of overlap is 8. The complementary parts are: non-unitary/squarefree set={2,6,22,26,66,78,286,828}, while the unitary/not squarefree set of equal size is {8,24,88,104,264,312,1144,3432}. So a(14)=8.
author: _Labos Elemer_, Aug 10 2000
